Perhaps you should have labeled this "Guacamole Sauce," since that's what it is with water added. True guacamole is mashed and always contains garlic. It usually contains tomatoes, as well, though they are not absolutely necessary. The primary taste should be lovely avocado (Haas are best) with the sharpness of lime, the headiness of garlic, and a hint of hot pepper. The most important thing is not to obscure the avodado, just to enhance it. Guacamole should not have the consistency of baby food, but should have a few tiny bits of the fruit still intact.

